<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="388" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,150,249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="388">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,187,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="388">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin “ 
<emphasis box="[879,976,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="388">arcuatus</emphasis>
” meaning “arched”, refers to the arched saccular process and arch˗shaped projection of tegumen in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
